Lagos State Traffic Radio, an agency of the state government, has concluded plans to organise the second edition of “Don’t drink and drive” road show. This is part of measures to ensure protection of lives and property. The agency called for the support and collaboration of well-meaning individuals and corporate bodies to ensure the success of the programme. A statement by the Head, Marketing, Mr. Dare Durosinmi, said the road show was a platform for creating awareness and educating motorists on the danger of drunk driving, in order to reduce accidents, especially during festive period. He said the event was scheduled to hold between November 23 and December 14 with a campaign train comprising officials of the Lagos State Drivers Institute (LASDRI), Lagos State Safety Commission (LSSC), Lagos State Traffic Management Authority (LASTMA) and Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) among others, visiting motor parks.